data.title: LIZZIE BRENNAN NAMED TO USA International surf rescue challenge Team — Ōrewa Surf Life Saving Club
data.meta_description: Elizabeth Brennan cements herself as one of the top athletes in the United States.
data.text:
After an outstanding weekend of racing at the USA Junior & U19 National Lifeguard Championships, held at Virginia Beach last weekend, Elizabeth Brennan cemented herself as one of the top athletes in the United States.

Lizzie claimed:

Gold in the U19 Iron & Ski

Silver in the Run Swim Run

Bronze in Board, Surf Race and 4-man Rescue events

As a result, Lizzie was named to the USA International Surf Rescue Challenge (ISRC) Team - Congratulations Lizzie!!

Lizzie will be joining club coach James Scott (racing for the NZ Black Fins) at the IISRC event, held in San Padre, Texas mid-September 2023.
